he Office Commencement Ceremony 2016 Graduation   Parents Letter Commencement is the culmination of four years of study at the Institute  The walk across the stage during this ceremony is a moment every graduate remembers  Anticipate heavy traffic  Parking is planned for the Parade Ground  Inclement weather could make the Parade Ground unavailable for parking  In the event of bad weather you may have to find alternate parking farther away  Notices will be posted on the VMI website with further information  Shuttle service will run continuously from Moody Hall to Cameron Hall beginning at 0800 a m  until 11 00 a m The shuttles will resume following the ceremony    The doors to Cameron Hall will open at 0930 Please arrive in time to be seated by 1045 Seating is on a first come  first served basis  Due to limited seating  no one will be admitted without a ticket  Due to space constraints and security reasons  coolers  backpacks and baskets are not allowed at any commencement ceremony location  Strollers must be able to be folded and out of the aisles  All carry in items are subject to search at the door  Wheelchair seating is available  Handicap drop off is located in front of Cameron Hall  Please email the Chief of Staff s Office at chiefofstaff vmi edu if you have certain handicap seating needs May Graduation Institute Awards Commissioning New Market Ceremony Graduation 2016 Ceremony Sen  Tim Kaine to Speak FAQs Media Resources Parking Info December Graduation Area Accommodations Katrina Butner Office Manager  or Col  Gary Bissell Deputy Chief of Staff and Operations P   540  464 7104 F   540  464 7660 201 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450 Email the Office  May Graduation Institute Awards Commissioning New Market Ceremony Graduation 2016 Ceremony Sen  Tim Kaine to Speak FAQs Media Resources Parking Info December Graduation Area Accommodations Katrina Butner Office Manager  or Col  Gary Bissell Deputy Chief of Staff and Operations P   540  464